s, inform\u00f3 el Minsa|date = 9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-04-10\n|5,897\n|4,210 <ref>{{Cite web | url=https://peru21.pe/peru/coronavirus-en-peru-aumenta-a-169-la-cifra-de-fallecidos-por-covid-19-en-nuestro-pais-segun-minsa-dia-26-hoy-10-de-abril-en-directo-vivo-online-ultimas-noticias-muertos-infectados-contagiados-ultimo-minuto-martin-vizcarra-minsa-minuto-a-minuto-del-covid-19-alerta-sos-estado-de-emergencia-cuarentena-online-noticia/ |title = Coronavirus en Per\u00fa: Aumenta a 169 la cifra de fallecidos por COVID-19 en nuestro pa\u00eds, seg\u00fan Minsa|date = 10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2020-04-11\n|6,848\n|4,933\n|-\n|2020-04-12\n|7,519\n|5,456\n|-\n|2020-04-13\n|9,784\n|7.458\n|-\n|2020-04-14\n|10,303\n|7,476\n|-\n|2020-04-15\n|11,475\n|8,412\n|-\n|2020-04-16\n|12,491\n|9,107\n|-\n|2020-04-17\n|13,489\n|9,793\n|-\n|2020-04-18\n|14,420\n|10,234\n|}\n\n==Statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+COVID-19 cases in Peru by region\nUpdated 18 April 2020<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gob.pe/institucion/minsa/noticias/112163-minsa-casos-confirmados-por-coronavirus-covid-19-ascienden-a-6-848-en-el-peru-comunicado-n-62|title=Minsa: Casos confirmados por coronavirus COVID-19 ascienden a 6 848 en el Per\u00fa (Comunicado N\u00b0 62)|website=www.gob.pe|language=es|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n!Region\n!Confirmed cases\n|-\n|[[Department of Amazonas, Peru|Amazonas]]\n|51\n|-\n|[[Department of Ancash|Ancash]]\n|217\n|-\n|[[Department of Apur\u00edmac|Apur\u00edmac]] \n|35\n|-\n|[[Department of Arequipa|Arequipa]]\n|146\n|-\n|[[Department of Ayacucho|Ayacucho]]\n|29\n|-\n|[[Department of Cajamarca|Cajamarca]]\n|52\n|-\n|[[Callao]]\n|1,180\n|-\n|[[Department of Cuzco|Cusco]]\n|123\n|-\n|[[Department of Huancavelica|Huancavelica]]\n|18\n|-\n|[[Department of Hu\u00e1nuco|Hu\u00e1nuco]] \n|64\n|-\n|[[Department of Ica|Ica]]\n|124\n|-\n|[[Department of Jun\u00edn|Jun\u00edn]] \n|130\n|-\n|[[Department of La Libertad|La Libertad]]\n|211\n|-\n|[[Department of Lambayeque|Lambayeque]]\n|642\n|-\n|[[Department of Lima|Lima]]\n|9,107\n|-\n|[[Department of Loreto|Loreto]]\n|485\n|-\n|[[Department of Madre de Dios|Madre de Dios]]\n|21\n|-\n|[[Department of Moquegua|Moquegua]]\n|28\n|-\n|[[Department of Pasco|Pasco]]\n|13\n|-\n|[[Department of Piura|Piura]]\n|344\n|-\n|[[Department of Puno|Puno]]\n|5\n|-\n|[[Department of San Mart\u00edn|San Mart\u00edn]]\n|81\n|-\n|[[Department of Tacna|Tacna]]\n|28\n|-\n|[[Department of Tumbes|Tumbes]]\n|86\n|-\n|[[Department of Ucayali|Ucayali]]\n|73\n|-\n|'''Total'''\n|'''14,420'''\n|}\n{{Medical cases chart\n    |barwidth=wide\n    |numwidth=mtmt\n    |float=none\n    |disease=COVID-19\n    |location=Peru\n    |data=|outbreak=2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic\n    |right2=# of deaths\n    |recoveries=y\n    |rows=\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-06|||1|||1||-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-07|||6|||6|+500%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-08|||7|||7|+17%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-09|||9|||9|+29%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-10|||11|||11|+22%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-11|||17|||17|+55%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-12|||22|||22|+29%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-13|||38|||38|+73%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-14|||43|||43|+13%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-15|||71|||71|+65%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-16|||86|||86|+21%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-17|||117|||117|+36%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-18|||145|||145|+24%|-||divisor=40|numwidth=mtmt}}\n      {{Medical cases chart/Row|2020-03-19|3||234|